dev:remarks.maml:para:
Gets all the slices for the table 'WikiAggregatedData' in the Azure data factory 'WikiADF' produced after 2014-05-20T10:00:00 (GMT). The availability for this table is set to "every hour" in the JSON file as shown below:
availability: { period: "Hour", periodMultiplier: 1 }
Notice that some of the artifacts are in Ready state and others are in the PendingExecution state. The ones in Ready state have already been executed and others are waiting for execution at the end of each hour in the interval specified by using the Set-AzureDataFactoryPipelineActivePeriod. In this example, both start and end periods for pipeline and slice are set to 1 day (24 hrs).

Gets the URL for HDInsight logs corresponding to the run for the data slice 'a7c4913c-9623-49b3-ae1e-3e45e2b68819'.

The following PowerShell script provides you an example to download HDInsight log files using the Shared Access Signature (SAS) token.

$OutputFolder=".\"

$resourceGroupName = "ADF"
$factoryName = "logprocessingfactory"
$startDate = "05/01/2014"
$tableName = "PartitionedGameEventsTable"

$run = Get-AzureDataFactoryRun -ResourceGroupName $resourceGroupName -DataFactoryName $factoryName -TableName $tableName -StartDateTime $startDate
$logInfo = Get-AzureDataFactoryRunLog -DataFactoryName $factoryName -ResourceGroupName $resourceGroupName -ID $run.{Id}

Write-Host "Slice ID: $run.{Id}"
$storageContext = New-AzureStorageContext  -StorageAccountName  $logInfo.{StorageAccountName} -SasToken $logInfo.{SasToken}

$downloadItems = Get-AzureStorageBlob -Container $logInfo.{Container} -Context $storageContext -Prefix ""

Write-Host "Downloading HDInsight logs "
foreach($blob in $downloadItems)
{
Write-Host $blob.Name
if($blob.Length -gt 0)
{
Get-AzureStorageBlobContent -Container $logInfo.{Container}  -Context $storageContext  -Blob $blob.Name  -Destination $OutputFolder -Force | Out-Null
}
}
